<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-07-31T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-07-31T08:00:00-05:00" n="872" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d872">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 341.622a/199</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-07-31T14:00:00+01:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 31, 1916, 2 p. m.</hi>
                                </date>
                                <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received August 1, 9.45 a.
                                m.</hi>]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>4637. Your 3562, July 24, 7 p. m. Lord <persName corresp="#p_GSE1">Grey</persName> informs me that telegraphic instructions have been
                            sent to Australia to release the <hi rend="italic">China</hi> prisoners
                            and that they will be put off as soon as can be decided upon what ship
                            they are to travel. I have also asked for detail of names, ages, status,
                            etc., of <hi rend="italic">China</hi> prisoners and similar information
                            regarding Leiztritz, Weinert, and Voik, removed from <hi rend="italic">Ausabls</hi> and <persName>
                                <hi rend="italic">Henry S.</hi>
                            </persName> and am promised this information [as] soon as possible.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_PWH1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Page</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>